Description: FRagment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Some light accretion may indicate a provenance other than Naukratis. Clay accreted. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '196', circled. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 51, 2? Name Aristratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0089.221.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1153)
